headline: Can Realty Income’s (O) Latest Dividend Hike Reveal More About Its Defensive Cash Flow Strategy?
summary: Realty Income recently raised its monthly dividend by 3.7%, marking the 111th consecutive quarterly increase for the real estate investment trust. This achievement highlights Realty Income's resilience, supported by its conservative financial strategy and focus on low-risk properties leased to tenants in recession-resistant industries. We'll now explore how this latest dividend increase could reinforce Realty Income's reputation for stable shareholder returns and defensive cash...
